    <div class="guide-content wow-panel">
        <div class="panel-header">Why Feral?</div>
        <div class="panel-content">
            <p>Feral Druids are one of TBC's most versatile melee DPS specs. As a Cat, you deal competitive melee damage while bringing Leader of the Pack (5% melee crit aura) to your group. The 0/47/14 build goes deep Feral for Mangle — your primary combo point generator that also debuffs the target for increased Bleed damage — while dipping into Restoration for Omen of Clarity (free ability procs) and Intensity for mana regeneration. Ferals can also off-tank in a pinch by shifting to Bear Form.</p>

            <h3>Key Talents</h3>
            <div class="talent-explanations">
                <div class="talent-explain">
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/ability_druid_mangle2.jpg" alt="Mangle" class="explain-icon">
                    <div>
                        <h4>Mangle (Cat)</h4>
                        <p>Mangle the target, inflicting damage and causing the target to take 30% additional damage from Bleed effects for 12 sec. Awards 1 combo point. Your bread-and-butter ability.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="talent-explain">
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/spell_nature_unyieldingstamina.jpg" alt="Leader of the Pack" class="explain-icon">
                    <div>
                        <h4>Leader of the Pack</h4>
                        <p>While in Cat or Bear Form, your critical strike chance and that of all party members within 45 yards is increased by 5%. Essential raid buff.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="talent-explain">
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/spell_nature_protectionformnature.jpg" alt="Survival of the Fittest" class="explain-icon">
                    <div>
                        <h4>Survival of the Fittest</h4>
                        <p>Increases all attributes by 3% and reduces the chance you'll be critically hit by melee attacks by 3%. Huge stat boost and crit immunity for tanking.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="talent-explain">
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/spell_shadow_vampiricaura.jpg" alt="Omen of Clarity" class="explain-icon">
                    <div>
                        <h4>Omen of Clarity</h4>
                        <p>Each melee hit has a chance of causing the caster to enter a Clearcasting state, making the next ability cost no mana, rage, or energy. Huge DPS and efficiency boost from the Restoration tree.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <h3>Stat Priority</h3>
            <ol>
                <li><strong>Hit Rating</strong> (until 9% / 142 rating)</li>
                <li><strong>Expertise</strong> (until 6.5% / 26 rating)</li>
                <li><strong>Agility</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Strength</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Critical Strike Rating</strong></li>
                <li><strong>Attack Power</strong></li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Rotation -->
    <div class="wow-panel">
        <div class="panel-header collapsible">Rotation / Ability Priority</div>
        <div class="panel-content accordion-body">
            <p class="section-intro">Feral Cat DPS in TBC revolves around maintaining Mangle's bleed debuff, building combo points with Shred from behind, and keeping Rip active. Powershifting (shifting out and back into Cat Form) with a Wolfshead Helm provides extra energy ticks for higher throughput.</p>
            <ol class="rotation-list">
                <li>
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/ability_druid_mangle2.jpg" alt="Mangle" class="rotation-icon" loading="lazy">
                    <div><span class="rotation-ability">Mangle (Cat)</span> — Apply and maintain the debuff (+30% bleed damage for 12s). Use as your primary combo point builder when Shred is unavailable.</div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/spell_shadow_vampiricaura.jpg" alt="Shred" class="rotation-icon" loading="lazy">
                    <div><span class="rotation-ability">Shred</span> — Main combo point builder. Must be used from behind the target. Higher damage than Mangle when the bleed debuff is already active.</div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/ability_ghoulfrenzy.jpg" alt="Rip" class="rotation-icon" loading="lazy">
                    <div><span class="rotation-ability">Rip</span> — Your primary finisher. Keep this DoT active at all times at 5 combo points. Benefits from the Mangle bleed debuff.</div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/ability_druid_disembowel.jpg" alt="Rake" class="rotation-icon" loading="lazy">
                    <div><span class="rotation-ability">Rake</span> — Use as a filler when Mangle debuff is active and you have energy to spare. Benefits from the Mangle bleed bonus.</div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/ability_druid_ferociousbite.jpg" alt="Ferocious Bite" class="rotation-icon" loading="lazy">
                    <div><span class="rotation-ability">Ferocious Bite</span> — Only use at 5 combo points when Rip is active with more than 8 seconds remaining. Dump excess combo points.</div>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <img src="https://wow.zamimg.com/images/wow/icons/medium/ability_mount_jungletiger.jpg" alt="Tiger's Fury" class="rotation-icon" loading="lazy">
                    <div><span class="rotation-ability">Tiger's Fury</span> — Use when energy is low for a burst of energy and bonus damage. Cannot be used while in Cat Form in TBC — use during powershifting.</div>
                </li>
            </ol>
        </div>
    </div>

